Terms and Conditions (T&C)

Last updated: 7 February 2026

1. Scope

These Terms and Conditions (T&C) apply to the use of the mobile application “Fraily” (hereinafter the “App”), operated by Nick Lehmacher (small business owner under the German “Kleinunternehmer” scheme) (hereinafter the “Provider”). By using the App, the user agrees to these T&C.

2. Description of Services

Fraily is an app for maintaining and managing social contacts. The App helps users keep track of their friendships, prepare conversation topics, and stay in regular contact with important people.

3. Registration and User Account

Use of the App does not require a traditional registration with email and password. User data is stored locally on the device. The user is responsible for the security of their device data.

4. Fraily Pro – Paid Subscription

The App offers a free basic version as well as a paid premium version (“Fraily Pro”).

4.1 Subscription

Fraily Pro is available as a subscription. Billing is handled via the respective app store (Apple App Store or Google Play Store). Prices are displayed transparently in the app store before purchase.

4.2 Term and Cancellation

The subscription renews automatically unless it is cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current subscription period. Cancellation can be done via the settings of the respective app store or within the App under “Settings” → “Manage Subscription”.

4.3 Right of Withdrawal

For in-app purchases, the withdrawal policies of the respective app store apply. The Provider notes that for digital content, the right of withdrawal may expire once performance has begun.

5. User Obligations

The user undertakes to use the App only for its intended purpose. Misuse of the App is prohibited, in particular entering content that violates applicable law or impairing the technical infrastructure of the App.

6. Availability

The Provider strives to ensure high availability of the App but does not guarantee uninterrupted use. Maintenance work, updates, or technical issues may temporarily restrict availability.

7. Liability

The Provider is only liable for damages caused by intent or gross negligence. Liability for minor negligence applies only in the event of a breach of essential contractual obligations. In this case, liability is limited to the foreseeable damage typical for the contract.

8. Data Protection

Protecting user data is important to the Provider. Details on the processing of personal data are governed by the Privacy Policy, which can be accessed within the App under “Settings” → “Privacy”.

9. Changes to the T&C

The Provider reserves the right to amend these T&C at any time. Users will be informed in good time of material changes. Continued use of the App after the changes take effect constitutes acceptance.

10. Final Provisions

The law of the Federal Republic of Germany shall apply. Place of jurisdiction is, insofar as legally permissible, Zirndorf. Should individual provisions of these T&C be invalid, the validity of the remaining provisions shall remain unaffected.

